r in Christian education, known for his groundbreaking research on the Book of Revelation and church leadership. Scholarly contributions included in the Festschrift mirror Fair’s own scholarly interests, including biblical studies, with particular attention to the New Testament apocalyptic traditions, philosophy of missions, theology of worship, history of the Restoration movement, and modern theology. The content of the Festschrift thus closely follows Fair's own spiritual and scholarly journey and also reflects the breadth and scope of his influence on the church and the academy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aTheology. 4aBible. 4aCriticism, Interpretation. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / General.2bisacsh1 aChilders, Jeffrey W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaughrity, Dyron B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlanders, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamilton, Mark W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Randy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeard, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuidobro, Tomas Garcia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCracken, Vic, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoney, Royce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrlov, Andrei A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrlov, Andrei, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aReese, Jack R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThompson, James W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.